Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Edible
    The purpose of this interface is to facilitate the determination of which objects a Jumper can remove by jumping on them.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BigPellet
    Represents an edible big pellet in the game, which fills 5 spaces on the board, and is worth more than a small pellet but less than a fruit.
    Board
    Creates a game board for the Pacman game.
    Cherry
    Represents an edible Cherry in the Pacman game, that appears for bonus points for a limited time in level 1.
    Fruit
    Represents an edible Fruit in the game, the designated superclass for all individual Fruit-type subclasses created within the Pacman class during the game.
    Game
    The class that initiates the game, by creating a specific board as per user input.
    Ghost
    Represents a Ghost character in the Pacman game Ghosts move around and turn randomly
    Orange
    Represents an edible Orange in the Pacman game, that appears for bonus points for a limited time in level 2.
    Pacman
    Represents a Pacman character in the Pacman game Pacman moves according to user input
    SmallPellet
    Represents an edible small pellet in the game, which fills all empty spaces of the board, and must all be eaten in order to win the game.
    Strawberry
    Represents an edible Strawberry in the Pacman game, that appears for bonus points for a limited time in level 3.
    Wall
    represents a Wall in the Pacman game.
    Watermelon
    Represents an edible Watermelon in the Pacman game, that appears for bonus points for a limited time in level 4.
